{"word":"ἀναίθω","slug":"ἀναίθω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀναίθω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to light up, set on fire</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: <i>to inflame</i> to love, <b><a href='S:Moschus'>Mosch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to blaze up</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}